SkillTotemId.description: """This links to SkillTotems.dat, but the number may exceed the number of entries; in that case it is player skill."""

Input_StatKeys.description: "Stats that will modify this skill specifically"

Output_StatKeys.description: "Stat an input stat will be transformed into"

VendorRecipe_AchievementItemsKeys.description: "Achievement check when selling this item to vendors"

Maximum_StatsKey.description: "Stat that holds the maximum number for this buff"

Current_StatsKey.description: "Stat that holds the current number for this buff"

Sockets.description: Number and colour of the sockets (in order).

Socketed_SkillGemsKeys.descriptions: Skill Gems socketed into the starting items

ModsKeys.description: Mods that are applied to the starting item

StackSize.description: The size of the stack, i.e. number of wisdom scrolls

FullStack_BaseItemTypesKey.description: Full stack transforms into this item

CharactersKeys.description: "Used for win as class mission types"

CooldownBypassType.description: 'Charge type to expend to bypass cooldown (Endurance, Frenzy, Power, none)'

StatsKeys2.description: Used with a value of one

DamageMultiplier.description: Damage multiplier in 1/10000 for attack skills

Sound.description: "Located in Audio/SoundEffects. Format has SG removed and $(#) replaced with the number"

MonsterVarietiesKey.description: Monster that plays the effect, i.e. the "nova" etc.

PositionX.description: X starts at left side of image, can be negative

PositionY.description: Y starts at top side of image, can be negative

Special_ModsKeys.description: "Keys for 'special' mods like untouchable by torment spirits."

Normal_AchievementItemsKeys.description: "Achievement objective awarded for killing this monster in normal difficulty"

Merciless_AchievementItemsKeys.description: "Achievement objective awarded for killing this monster in merciless difficulty"

Cruel_AchievementItemsKeys.description: "Achievement objective awarded for killing this monster in cruel difficulty"

PhysicalItemPoints.description: "Number of points the user gets back if they opt-out of physical items"

BuffStatValues.description: For use for the related stat in the buff.
